%% ModelMesh Serving - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant OAuth as oauth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS serving cert
    participant REST as rest-proxy<br/>8008/TCP HTTP
    participant Ctrl as Controller
    participant MM as ModelMesh<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant MMB as ModelMesh Pod B
    participant Puller as Storage Helper puller
    participant Server as Model Server Container
    participant etcd as etcd<br/>2379/TCP gRPC
    participant S3 as Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Server: Flow 1 - gRPC Inference Direct
    Client->>MM: gRPC inference request<br/>8033/TCP Optional TLS/mTLS
    MM->>Server: Forward to model server<br/>unix socket or TCP plaintext
    Server-->>MM: Prediction result
    MM-->>Client: gRPC response

    Note over Client,Server: Flow 2 - REST Inference via OAuth
    Client->>OAuth: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS Bearer token
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate token via<br/>OpenShift SAR check
    OAuth->>REST: Forward request<br/>8008/TCP HTTP pod-local
    REST->>MM: Translate to gRPC<br/>8033/TCP Optional TLS
    MM->>Server: Forward to model server<br/>plaintext pod-local
    Server-->>MM: Prediction result
    MM-->>REST: gRPC response
    REST-->>OAuth: HTTP response
    OAuth-->>Client: HTTPS response

    Note over Ctrl,S3: Flow 3 - Model Registration and Loading
    Ctrl->>MM: VModel register<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    MM->>etcd: Store model placement<br/>2379/TCP Basic auth
    MM->>Puller: Load model request<br/>8086/TCP gRPC pod-local
    Puller->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>443/TCP HTTPS S3 credentials
    S3-->>Puller: Model artifacts
    Puller-->>MM: Model loaded
    MM->>etcd: Update model state

    Note over MM,etcd: Flow 4 - Inter-Pod Model Routing
    MM->>etcd: Query model placement<br/>2379/TCP
    MM->>MMB: Route inference to Pod B<br/>8080/TCP gRPC LiteLinks plaintext

    Note over Ctrl,K8s: Flow 5 - Controller Reconciliation
    K8s-->>Ctrl: Watch events CR changes<br/>443/TCP HTTPS SA token
    Ctrl->>K8s: Create/Update Deployments<br/>Services ConfigMaps
    Ctrl->>etcd: Event stream monitoring<br/>2379/TCP Basic auth
